Psalm 142

2 With all my vóice I crý to the LÓRD;
with all my vóice I entréat the LÓRD.
3 I póur out my tróuble befóre him;
I téll him áll my distréss
4 while my spírit fáints withín me.
But yóu, O LÓRD, know my páth.

On the wáy where Í shall wálk,
they have hídden a snáre to entráp me.
5 Lóok on my right hánd and sée:
there is nó one who páys me héed.
No escápe remains ópen to mé;
nó one cáres for my sóul.

6 To yóu I crý, O LÓRD.
I have said, ``Yóu are my réfuge,
my pórtion in the lánd of the líving."
7 Lísten, thén, to my crý,
for Í am brought dówn very lów.

Réscue me from thóse who pursúe me,
for théy are strónger than Í.
8 Bríng my sóul out of príson,
and Í shall give thánks to your náme.
Aróund me the júst will assémble,
becáuse of your góodness to mé.
